            <subject>Re: slide 12: Comparison of output equation and state equation</subject>
            <message>&lt;p&gt;The correspondence is between what is estimated and what is measured.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the full order estimator, all the states are estimated and y is the output.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the reduced order estimator, what is not measured is estimated (xb) and a function of measured states (xa) is the output.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The correspondence is between (1) estimator equations and (2) output equations.&lt;/p&gt;</message>
