            <subject>Re:slide 22</subject>
            <message>&lt;p&gt;When the poles of the estimator are chosen to be at the origin.  The response is of the form $$e=a^n$$, where $$e$$ is the error, $$a$$ is the pole location and $$n$$ is the sampling instant.  The time taken for $$e$$ to reach zero is nil.  This provides the fastest response possible. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is an example of dead beat controller in the book.  Please read it.&lt;/p&gt;</message>
